data.description: When the `type` is `HEADER`, specify the name of the header that you want to search using the `data` field, for example, `User-Agent` or `Referer`. If the `type` is any other value, you can omit this field.

type.description: Part of the web request that you want AWS WAF to search for a specified string. For example, `HEADER`, `METHOD`, or `BODY`. See the [docs](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/waf/latest/APIReference/API_FieldToMatch.html) for all supported values.
